---
By: Henry T. Hamblin
Locus:
  Page: 194
  Verse: 3
Tags:
  - God
---
Some who have no knowledge of the subject, say that to surrender to the
will of God is an act of weakness. They should try it and see for
themselves. They would then find that they had taken on “a man’s job,” and
there is no life that calls for so much courage and faith as that which
seeks to be led according to the will of God.
